transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey James, yes. Hey, bud. Thank you so much for holding. So I did three things for you.

Speaker 2: I did exactly what you wanted and you needed. The first thing I did is I put a stop to any and all—

Speaker 1: Monthly deals. And the second thing I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly shipments. And the third thing I did—

Speaker 2: Is I put a stop to any and all monthly charges and I sent an email to Dr.

Speaker 1: And I set up your dashboard because I paused your prescription. And the way that looks is when you get a chance, go to—

Speaker 2: Scoreblue.com on your browser, your Google browser or your navigator.

Speaker 1: Okay, log in with your Yahoo account. When you log in with your Yahoo account—

Speaker 2: You're gonna see in the category your prescription.

Speaker 1: I put a red button with white font that says "Quick Refill Now." Anytime, anywhere in the future—

Speaker 2: Should you need more, you click that button. We'll send it to you, okay, and two to three business days.

Speaker 1: I couldn't stop what was already in process, but I also put a—and I apologize about that—

Speaker 2: It was too late.

Speaker 1: It's already being labeled and shipped and there's a tracking number.

Speaker 2: But I did put a button, a blue button that you can click that can—takes you to—

Speaker 1: The USPS page where you can track it. Okay, should get it by Monday or Tuesday, but just hold on to those.

Speaker 2: Because we're all sold out of the hundreds. And if you need something else, like something stronger or anything else, you call me at—

Speaker 1: Zero zero three seven. Did you call the pharmacy? Did you call us? I—

Speaker 2: Called you and I wrote them. They told me to call you. Yeah, so just dial zero zero three seven, bud.

Speaker 1: Okay, and that way if you need anything in the future, deal with me because my fingerprints are on this and as a veteran—

Speaker 2: Pride and honor in my work, but in—

Speaker 1: Okay, everything you need it, but enough. Have fun. We're not here for a long time. We're here for a good time, but in—

Speaker 2: God bless you, right? Okay. God bless you. Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, yes.

Speaker 2: Mark, yeah, 1124. Therefore I say to you, brother James, whatever things you ask when you pray—

Speaker 1: Believe that you receive them and they—you will have them. In Jesus' mighty name. All right, brother. God bless you. God bless you.
